title: Ferroud - Sym in A - Davin, Wurttemberg Phil Orch [Philidor]
description:
Pierre-Octave Ferroud was an outstanding composer and critic whose life was cut short at the age of 35, in an automobile accident in Debrecen, Hungary. A Frenchman, the aesthetics of both Ravel and the more satirical members of Les Six interested him--Ravel more so around and after 1930, when his works grew increasingly less traditional. 

Transfers are made at 768 kBits/s, directly from the disc.
